Offering Profile

Overview/Objectives 
Strategy 
Risk Factors 




Investment Goals and Objectives
NYC REIT seeks to create value for shareholders through the execution of the following goals and objectives:

Maximize Total Shareholder Returns through a combination of realized appreciation and current income.
Pay Distributions out to shareholders on a monthly basis1
Maintain Low Leverage - financing the portfolio at a target level of not more than 40% to 50% loan-to-value
Target a Potential Liquidity Event within three to six years from the close of initial offering2
New York City Focus to acquire high-quality commercial real estate located in the five boroughs of New York City, and in particular, Manhattan
Diversified Tenant Mix leased to a diversified group of tenants with a bias toward lease terms of five years or greater




(1) Distributions are not guaranteed. A portion of the distributions paid in cash has exceeded cumulative cash flow from operations and has been paid out of cash on hand and proceeds from the IPO.
(2) If the board does not decide to purse a liquidity event, or the stockholders do not approve a liquidity event, we could continue to operate indefinitely.























